    "id": 3463803,
    "postDate": "2026-05-27T22:56:59.323Z",
    "rawMarkdown": "Hmm, I also have this issue and it seems to be due to a reset of the daily submission limit to 5. Kaggle enforces an overall submission limit of days_since_start * submission_limit to prevent teams that merge late from having had many more than 5 submissions per day on average. Since days_since_start = 43 and the default submission limit is 5, this matches perfectly: 43 * 5 = 215. Not sure why it was reduced but in any case, I hope if the host plans to actually plans to keep this limit, it will be handled properly with respect to the previous submissions made.",
    "content": "<p>Hmm, I also have this issue and it seems to be due to a reset of the daily submission limit to 5. Kaggle enforces an overall submission limit of days_since_start * submission_limit to prevent teams that merge late from having had many more than 5 submissions per day on average. Since days_since_start = 43 and the default submission limit is 5, this matches perfectly: 43 * 5 = 215. Not sure why it was reduced but in any case, I hope if the host plans to actually plans to keep this limit, it will be handled properly with respect to the previous submissions made.</p>",
